PowerBalance / balruno — Repository License Overview
=====================================================

This repository uses different licenses for different components.
See `LICENSING.md` for a developer-friendly explanation, or read each
directory's LICENSE file for the authoritative legal text.

Directory                License       Why
-----------------------  ------------  -----------------------------------------
packages/web/            MIT           Browser-executed Next.js app. Free to
                                       fork, embed, or reuse without
                                       restriction. See: packages/web/LICENSE
packages/shared/         MIT           Platform-agnostic shared code (types +
                                       game-domain logic: formulas, simulation,
                                       analysis). Reused by web/desktop/(future
                                       mobile). See: packages/shared/LICENSE
packages/desktop/        MIT           Electron desktop app. Bundles
                                       packages/web build output. Open for fork
                                       and self-build. See: packages/desktop/LICENSE
packages/backend/ (TBD)  AGPL v3       Server code (Spring Boot). Self-host
                                       freely; if you modify and offer as a
                                       service to others, you must publish your
                                       changes. Created at Phase B-1 bootstrap.
docs/ (public files)     MIT           Same as packages/web. (docs/backend/
                                       and docs/archive/ are kept private via
                                       .gitignore — internal design notes.)

The historical project-wide MIT license (Copyright (c) 2025 Balruno) applies
to all code committed before 2026-05-03. The license split above takes effect
for files added on or after 2026-05-03 per ADR 0005
(`docs/backend/decisions/0005-oss-monetization.md`).

For the trademark "PowerBalance" and "balruno", and the project logo, see
`TRADEMARK.md`. These are NOT covered by the source code licenses above.

For commercial licensing inquiries (e.g. embedding the AGPL backend in a
proprietary product without AGPL obligations), contact: dj258255@naver.com
